Developer Portfolio Landing Page — Terminal/Hacker
Aesthetic

CATEGORY

Personal Portfolio / Developer

DESIGN STYLE

Terminal green-on-black, monospace typography, CRT scaniines, blinking cursors, command-ine Ul
elements

Overview

Build an atmospheric developer portfolio landing page for ‘Alex Chen — Full Stack Engineer’. The
design mimics a terminal/command-ine interface with a pure black background (¥0D0DOD), phosphor
green (#00FF41) as the primary accent, and JetBrains Mono for all text. The hero renders as a fake

terminal with commands being typed. Sections appear as if printed by a command. CRT scanline effect
applied as a CSS pseudo-element. No images — all visuals are ASCII art, ASCII borders, and
monospace Ul elements. The effect should feel like you've SSHd into a hacker's personal server.
Design Tokens
Background #0DODOD — Near-black terminal
Primary Text #EBEBES — Soft white
Accent Green #00FF41 — Phosphor green for prompts, highlights
Dim Green #006614 — Dimmed, for less important terminal output
Warning #FFD700 — Yellow for caution/alerts
Error #FF4444 — Red for error output
Typography JetBrains Mono ONLY — 14px base, no decorative fonts
Radius Opx everywhere
CRT Effect Scanlines via repeating-linear-gradient pseudo-element
Page Sections
1. Boot Sequence Intro (Skip-able)
~ On first load: 2-second boot sequence animation — green text lines print rapidly: BIOS v2.4.1 ... Loading
kemel .. Mounting filesystem _."

— Framer Motion staggered line reveals, 50ms between each

~ "SKIP INTRO button appears after 0.55 — pressing it Framer Motion exit animations to main page

2. Terminal Hero
~ Fake terminal window with title bar showing three circles (red/yellow/green) and path ~/portiolio

~ Command prompt: alex@portiolio:~$ followed by animated typewriter revealing Whoami’

~ Output prints below: ASCII art of name + role + location

— Next prompt types Is skills" and outputs a grid of technologies.

— Blinking cursor CSS animation: opacity 01-0 at 1s interval
~~ — Scrolldown indicator green : blinkingarrow

3. Projects — as ‘Is -la’ output
— Section header: alex@portiolio-~$ Is -la projects! printed with typewriter
— Each project as a file listing row: permissions + size + date + project-name.md
— Clicking a project: expands inline as if cat project md — shows description, tech stack, links
— Framer Motion AnimatePresence for the expandicollapse
4. Skills — ASCII Progress Bars
— Each skill: Reacts (I 1 85% — pure ASCII progress bars.
— Framer Motion animates the fill on scroll entry: empty — filled, 1s duration each, staggered
— Categories: Frontend / Backend / DevOps / Tools — each section preceded by a comment line '#
Frontend’
5. Work History — as log file
— Title: ‘experience log’

— Each job entry formatted as log output with timestamps: [2022-03-01 09:00:00] START JOB: Senior
Engineer at Acme Corp
— Details as indented log lines
6. Contact — Interactive Terminal
— Actual input field styled as terminal prompt: alex@portfolio-~$ send-message
— User types name, email, message as prompted — one field at a time
~ On submit: ‘Message sent. / Transmission complete."
— Framer Motion: each input fades in as previous is completed
Animations
— Alltext: typewriter character-by-character reveal using setTimeout
~ Cursor: CSS animation blink at 1s interval
— Section reveals: Framer Motion whilelnView opacity 0 1, no movement (terminal lines just appear)
— ASCII progress bars: Framer Motion animate width percentage   
